    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-04-22T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-04-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="61"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d61">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.51/300</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Commercial Adviser of the British Embassy</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Crawford</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-04-22">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 22, 1918</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Sir <persName>Richard</persName>
                    </hi>: I have your letter of March 23, 1918, in which you inquire the views of
                    this Government in regard to Russian funds in this country. Up to the present
                    time the status of Mr. <persName corresp="#p_BBA1">Boris Bakhmeteff</persName>,
                    as Ambassador, representing the Provisional Government of Russia, and the
                    propriety of his controlling such funds as may be available to him in this
                    country in that capacity have not been questioned.</p>
                <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
